        <Document ID="FCE9BE52-049B-440C-BC1A-057D83831EB0">
            <Title>1B: EVERYTHING CHANGES</Title>
            <Text>1B: EVERYTHING CHANGES

Two big things should be happening here, though they don’t have to be in the same scene. First, a Big Problem is going to change everything in terms of your character’s outer layer of the story. Second, C1 meets C2. (If they already know each other, this is the first time they meet in your story and it could be the first time they’re having a romantic spark with each other.)

It’s extremely important to make the meeting memorable and it depends on your tone and sub-genre whether the meeting is funny, angsty, steamy or something else. You should show your readers how these two people absolutely belong together but also how they’re impossibly incompatible at the same time, for whatever reason. You can also show how their external goals don’t work together, like maybe they work in competing bookstores. Although they should be finding each other attractive, your characters should not want to pursue a relationship with each other.
</Text>
        </Document>
