        <Document ID="4FF08460-0BFC-41C2-85A1-4C2712B612DB">
            <Title>2D: DRAMATIC EVENT AT MIDPOINT</Title>
            <Text>2D: DRAMATIC EVENT AT MIDPOINT
Something big always needs to happen in the middle of the story, whether it’s a new disaster or learning information that changes everything. That’s for the external layer of your story.

 When it comes to the external layer, you could have a false victory OR an apparent defeat, but when it comes to the inner layer that deals with the characters’ love life, it has to be a false victory. They’ve been more intimate than ever - and you want true, emotional intimacy - and they think they really have won the relationship lottery. (If they just slept together with feeling, that could be the midpoint event. Alternatively, having a heartfelt conversation about it could be the midpoint. Whichever is the bigger event.) 

Everything feels so right, but the problem is… they still haven’t dealt with their existing problems. They’ve just covered them up with all the infatuation. Make sure that they’re so high up in the clouds that falling down is really going to hurt.</Text>
