        <Document ID="038216C0-653E-45D4-9588-72E8D19C4001">
            <Title>3B: RETREAT FROM EACH OTHER</Title>
            <Text>3B: RETREAT FROM EACH OTHER
The doubts and fears win. Your characters are so afraid of getting hurt that giving each other a chance becomes impossible and they retreat from each other. Unlike sensible people, they don’t talk about their worries with each other, but they do (or at least C1 does) admit to someone why they’re doing this.

All their doubts and excuses have become a self-fulfilling prophecy - or at least that’s what C1 and C2 think. They’re certain they’ve been right all along and should have seen it coming, though most likely they’ve misunderstood something or are just seeing things through the lense of their worst fears. They feel like they’ve deserved all this pain because they were silly enough to let their guard down, but they swear not to make the same mistake ever again.
</Text>
