        <Document ID="68393C55-1718-4F87-9739-68D21440722D">
            <Title>3C: DISASTER STRIKES</Title>
            <Text>3C: DISASTER STRIKES
For your external plot, this is where the very worst happens. Maybe the bookstore’s opening day is a disaster or maybe the murderer escapes from right under their noses. In other words, your character should be hitting rock bottom.

It is equally catastrophic for the romance layer of the story. Maybe they just broke up in the previous scene and they’re now having a heated screaming match at the local Starbucks, but whatever it is, it needs to be an equal rock bottom moment. It can happen at the same time as the external disaster, but even if they happen at different times, both events need to be caused by your character’s flaws and misconceptions.

There is always a choice between fear and love, and at least one of your characters needs to choose fear at this point in the story. It’s extremely important that it’s a CHOICE and not something that’s enforced from the outside.
</Text>
